      "description": "UAE intercepts Iranian missiles; Strait of Hormuz oil flow drops 30% instantly.",
      "details": "The UAE military confirmed intercepting ballistic missiles over the Persian Gulf, a massive escalation in the 2026 Iran War. Tanker traffic through the Strait of Hormuz immediately dropped by 30%, triggering fears of a global energy crisis. Such geopolitical 'shocks' dominate social feeds and shift consumer focus from shopping to news consumption. This likely contributed to the CPA spike ($33-$36) seen in the following days.",
