      "description": "April CPI hits 3.8%; energy costs up 17.9% and gas up 28.4%.",
      "details": "The Bureau of Labor Statistics released the April CPI showing inflation exceeding expectations at 3.8% annually. Energy costs were the primary driver, serving as a 'wallet reminder' to consumers during their morning news routine. For a specialty food brand with a ~$45 AOV, these reports trigger discretionary spending pullbacks. High CPAs ($33.62) on this date correlate with the negative headline cycle.",
